  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cholera Prevention and Response through French Red Cross</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal is to contribute to the elimination of cholera from Haiti by strengthening the capacities of HRC in support of the efforts of MSPP in prevention, response and communication related to the cholera epidemic. This goal will be achieved through the following objectives:  

Risks of transmission and exposure to cholera are reduced through improved access to potable water and increase knowledge regarding hygiene and sanitation amongst the targeted communities

The system of investigation and response to alerts/spikes of cholera cases is functional in the areas of intervention.

Haitian Red Cross is strengthened in its auxiliary role towards the MSPP by providing epidemiological and investigation/response data through the national cholera alert and epidemiological surveillance systems.</narrative>
  </description>
